issues.body:
This is an issue reproducible with the very simple example [transcriber.py](https://github.com/livekit-examples/python-agents-examples/blob/main/pipeline-stt/transcriber.py), using the latest version of livekit agents ([1.1.0](https://github.com/livekit/agents/releases/tag/livekit-agents%401.1.0)).

If you modify the `WorkerOptions` to include the `hidden` property in the `WorkerPermissions` object like this:

```python
if __name__ == "__main__":
    cli.run_app(WorkerOptions(
            entrypoint_fnc=entrypoint,
            permissions=WorkerPermissions(hidden=True)
     ))
```

Then any frontend trying to receive the transcription text stream exactly as documented [here](https://docs.livekit.io/agents/build/text/#frontend-integration) will receive the `participantInfo.identity` as an empty string. In other words: this...

```javascript
room.registerTextStreamHandler('lk.transcription', async (reader, participantInfo) => {
  const message = await reader.readAll();
  if (reader.info.attributes['lk.transcribed_track_id']) {
    console.log(`New transcription from ${participantInfo.identity}: ${message}`);
  } else {
    console.log(`New message from ${participantInfo.identity}: ${message}`);
  }
});
```

...will print...

```console
New transcription from : Good morning.
```

I think this is a bug, because why should the `hidden` property of the `WorkerPermissions` affect whether the transcription events arrive with a valid participant identity value or not? This `participantInfo.identity` belongs to the participant owning the track that generated the transcription event. Nothing related to the Agent participant itself, whether it is hidden or not.

`MultimodalLLMMetrics` is missing `cached_tokens_details` from the original OpenAI realtime usage metrics response. Here is the full response example (spec here: https://platform.openai.com/docs/api-reference/realtime-server-events/response/done):
```
{
      "total_tokens":275,
      "input_tokens":127,
      "output_tokens":148,
      "input_token_details": {
          "cached_tokens":384,
          "text_tokens":119, 
          "audio_tokens":8,

          # this block is required to compute the pricing for the request since some cached tokens are text whereas some are audio
          "cached_tokens_details": { 
              "text_tokens": 128,
              "audio_tokens": 256
          }
      },
      "output_token_details": {
         "text_tokens":36,
         "audio_tokens":112
      }
}
```

It would also be nice if UsageCollector supports the full MultimodalLLMMetrics, but I can pretty easily roll my own there since its just an aggregator.

Using with Azure gpt-4o-mini-realtime-preview model (api_version="2024-10-01-preview") leads to an error:

`ERROR livekit.plugins.openai - OpenAI Realtime API returned an error {"error": "Error(message=\"Unknown parameter: 'session.tracing'.\", type='invalid_request_error', code='unknown_parameter', event_id='session_update_5bfd853a8dfe', param='session.tracing')"}`

@mikevin920

