issues.body:
Hi everyone,
Since I moved to v1.0, something weird started happening with transcriptions

This issue is reproducible on 1.0.20 and probably lower (livekit agents and deepgram plugin)

I'm using Deepgram STT with interim transcriptions
The issue was not reproducing on other providers that I've tried

Here is my frontend code that captures 'lk.transcription':
```
this.room?.registerTextStreamHandler('lk.transcription', async (reader, participantInfo) => {
        const { data } = useAuth();
        const userEmail = data?.value?.user?.email;

        console.log('segmentId', segmentId, reader.info.attributes["lk.transcription_final"]);
        for await (const chunk of reader) {
          console.log('chunk', chunk);
          if (userEmail && participantInfo.identity === userEmail) {
            processMessageV2(segmentId, chunk, 'human');
          } else {
            processMessageV2(segmentId, chunk, 'bot');
          }
        }
      });
```

Basically, captures user transcriptions and adds them to the chat on the frontend. 
`processMessageV2` function decides how to add the newly incoming chunk: 
1. If the segment ID of a new chunk was already in the chat, it replaces it with a new chunk text, since it is supposed to be updated interim result (e.g., `{"segment_id": "SG_123", "text": "Hello"}, {"segment_id": "SG_123", "text": "Hello, how"}, {"segment_id": "SG_123", "text": "Hello, how are you?"}`)
2. If the segment ID of a new chunk was never in the chat before, it adds a new chat item, since it doesn't contain parts of previous chunks.

In most cases, it works well. However, consider the following case:

I tried to say something like this to an Agent: "That sounds incredibly frustrating! Dealing with intermittent bugs can be really draining..."

The console logs are:

<img width="465" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/57462e05-2d68-40aa-a42d-b0473c476d83" />

And the chat on the frontend looks like this:

<img width="425" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0ecb45fb-e957-48e8-9efd-4090b6dc4b70" />

As you can see in the logs, "That sounds incredibly frustrating! Dealing with" was actually transcribed by the STT (and even appeared in the chat for a couple of seconds). However, it was violently replaced by the "internal bugs".

This happened because the "internal bugs" chunk had the same segment ID in the reader info as all the previous interim transcriptions, without including the previous chunks' text. And then normal transcription was continued.

So I'm generally confused about what identifier to use now to understand when to ADD a new chat item and when to REPLACE previous ones on interim results. 

Previously, on v0.x, transcriptions had the ID, which worked perfectly in this scenario. 

I double-checked both Deepgram plugin's SpeechStream and stt_node and found that the `reader.info.attributes["lk.transcription_final"]` seems to be misleading. The chunks classified as "final" are often returned on the frontend as non-final.

So, for me, it seems to be an issue with the layer above the stt_node, which is packing the STT Events in segments for the frontend.

Reproducibility of this issue is ~10%, increasing with long inputs (3-5 sentences). However, in real conversations I found this quite often, which really breaks the experience. 

I also found kinda similar issue with long audio inputs on [Retell.AI](https://www.retellai.com/) interface. I'm not sure if these issues are directly related, but their transcriptions often disappear on long inputs. 

Looking forward to your thoughts on this
Let me know if you need any more info!

